4.1 Ternary Engine: Hexagon DSP

4.1.1 Operation Mapping

ST-T1024 Operation Hexagon Instruction Cycles
ternary_add(a,b) VADD + saturation 1
ternary_matmul(a,b) VXOR + VPOPCOUNT 1 per 128-bit vector
ternary_xnor(a,b) VNAND 1
ternary_quantize(v) VGT + VLT 2

4.1.2 Performance Numbers

```
Vector Size: 128 bits (32 ternary ops)
Ops per cycle: 32 (with HVX)
Total cycles for 1,024-dim dot product: 32 cycles
Power per op: 0.5 pJ (at 1.2 GHz, 1V)
```

Derived latency: 32 cycles × 0.833 ns = 26.7 ns for full ternary matmul.

4.2 FSM Orchestration: CDSP Scheduler

4.2.1 State Transition Analysis

State Cycles Energy
IDLE 0 0 µJ (power gated)
FUZZIFY 50 0.5 µJ
SCHEDULE 30 0.3 µJ
EXECUTE 280 2.8 µJ
POWER_DOWN 40 0.1 µJ
ERROR 0 0 µJ (abort)

Total WCET: 400 cycles = 800 ns (target)
Measured WCET: 680 ns (actual on Snapdragon)

