6. Scalability Analysis

6.1 1/N Energy Scaling

For N domain tiles, each with average size S:

```
Traditional: E_total = N × S × P (all tiles active)
ST-T1024: E_total = S × P (only 1 tile active)

Savings: 1/N (linear improvement with more tiles)
```

6.2 Real-World Projections

Tiles Energy/Query Throughput Applications
4 3.7 µJ 1.47M QPS General purpose
16 0.9 µJ 5.88M QPS Domain-specific
64 0.2 µJ 23.5M QPS Ultra-narrow domains
256 0.05 µJ 94M QPS Edge/embedded sensors

6.3 Memory Scalability

```
ROM: 75% of total weights
SRAM: 25% of total weights
Total memory per tile: S (size of tile's ROM + SRAM)

Total system memory: N × S (all tiles) but only S active.
```

Key insight: Memory footprint grows with N, but active memory is always S.

