9.3 The Verification Principle

In a deterministic architecture, simulation = execution.

This benchmark demonstrates that ST-T1024's claims are computable from hardware specifications. No physical measurement is required because:

1. All operations are bounded (WCET)
2. All cycles are known (FSM states)
3. All energy is linear (no stochastic variance)
4. All outputs are reproducible (no randomness)

The architecture is the guarantee.

